  "prompt": "Will yongnuo RF 603 ii RF triggers allows High speed sync triggering?",
  "response": "The Yongnuo RF-603 II triggers do not support high-speed sync (HSS). The RF-603 II triggers are basic transceivers designed for standard wireless flash triggering, typically supporting shutter speeds up to the camera's maximum sync speed (usually around 1/200 or 1/250 second). If you need high-speed sync capabilities, you would need to look into other Yongnuo models that specifically advertise HSS support, such as the Yongnuo YN-622 series or the YN-560-TX/RF-605 when used with compatible flashes.",
